      "content": "I understand your frustration, and I apologize for the goblin overload. You are absolutely right; we can get straight to the science without the extra noise.\n\nHere is the direct breakdown of the **light-dependent reactions** and the **Calvin Cycle** regarding ATP and NADPH:\n\n**1. Light-Dependent Reactions (The \"Power Plant\")**\n*   **Location:** Thylakoid membranes in the chloroplast.\n*   **Input:** Light energy + Water ($H_2O$).\n*   **Process:** Light energy excites electrons, which travel down an electron transport chain. This movement pumps protons ($H^+$) into the thylakoid space, creating a gradient.\n*   **Outputs:**\n    *   **ATP:** Created via chemiosmosis as protons flow back out through ATP synthase.\n    *   **NADPH:** Created when electrons (carrying high-energy electrons) are transferred to NADP+ at the end of the chain.\n    *   **Oxygen:** Released as a byproduct when water is split.\n\n**2. The Calvin Cycle (The \"Factory\")**\n*   **Location",
